{% extends "_base.html.j2" %}

{% block content %}
<section class="container">

  <nav class="breadcrumbs" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
    <a href="/">Home</a><span>/</span>
    <span>Sources & Methodology</span>
  </nav>

  <header style="margin: 16px 0 24px;">
    <div style="font-size:12px; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:1.4px; color:#cc0000; font-weight:700;">
      Methodology · Authority signal
    </div>
    <h1 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:36px; color:var(--sr-blue-dark); margin:8px 0 12px;">
      Sources & Methodology
    </h1>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-style:italic; color:var(--sr-gray-text); font-size:18px;">
      Every briefing on Caracas Research is derived from primary
      Venezuelan-government, US-government, and international monitoring
      sources — refreshed twice daily, with full provenance kept for each
      data point.
    </p>
  </header>

  <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); color:var(--sr-blue-dark); margin: 32px 0 16px;">Primary sources we monitor</h2>

  <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:1fr; gap:16px; margin-bottom:32px;">
    {% for s in sources %}
    <article style="border:1px solid var(--sr-gray-light); border-left:4px solid var(--sr-blue); padding:18px 22px; border-radius:3px;">
      <div style="display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:flex-start; gap:16px; flex-wrap:wrap;">
        <div>
          <h3 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:18px; color:var(--sr-blue-dark);">{{ s.name }}</h3>
          <div style="font-size:12px; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.6px; color:var(--sr-gray-text); margin-top:2px;">
            {{ s.kind }} · {{ s.tier }}
          </div>
        </div>
        {% if s.entries_count is not none %}
        <div style="background:var(--sr-gray-bg); padding:6px 12px; border-radius:3px; font-size:13px; color:var(--sr-blue-dark); font-weight:600; white-space:nowrap;">
          {{ s.entries_count }} entries on file
        </div>
        {% endif %}
      </div>
      <p style="margin-top:10px; color:var(--sr-dark-text); font-size:15px;">{{ s.description }}</p>
      <div style="margin-top:8px; font-size:13px;">
        <strong>Refresh cadence:</strong> {{ s.cadence }} ·
        <a href="{{ s.url }}" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">View source &rarr;</a>
      </div>
    </article>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>

  <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); color:var(--sr-blue-dark); margin:32px 0 12px;">How we use these sources</h2>
  <p>Each scrape run pulls fresh content from the sources above, deduplicates against what we've already seen, and runs the resulting items through a multi-stage filter:</p>
  <ol style="margin:12px 0 16px 24px;">
    <li><strong>Keyword pre-filter</strong> drops items that don't mention Venezuela-relevant entities, sectors, programs, or named officials. About 70% of incoming items get dropped at this step.</li>
    <li><strong>Tone score</strong> from GDELT (where applicable) is used to prioritise items that read as either materially negative or materially positive — neutral wire copy is deprioritized.</li>
    <li><strong>Editorial scoring</strong> assigns a 1-10 investor-relevance score, an English headline, sector tags, sentiment, and an investor takeaway. Items scoring below 5 are not published. Scoring runs only on items that survive the first two filters.</li>
    <li><strong>Long-form analysis</strong> (the <a href="/briefing">/briefing</a> posts) is produced for items scoring 5+.</li>
    <li><strong>Investment guides and sector pages</strong> (<a href="/invest-in-venezuela">/invest-in-venezuela</a> and <a href="/sectors/mining">/sectors/*</a>) are refreshed on a weekly cadence.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); color:var(--sr-blue-dark); margin:32px 0 12px;">Editorial standards</h2>
  <p>This site is independent commentary by an analyst team, not investment advice. Every page links back to the primary source so you can verify the underlying facts before acting. We publish corrections in the next scheduled briefing window when errors are identified.</p>

  <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); color:var(--sr-blue-dark); margin:32px 0 12px;">Get in touch</h2>
  <p>Found a factual error, want to suggest a source, or interested in syndication? Reply to any briefing email or subscribe below for the daily digest.</p>

</section>
{% endblock %}
